= Oral Immunotherapy (OIT): hand-out
== What is OIT?
OIT is a medical treatment for food allergies that helps patients gradually gain tolerance to the allergen. By slowly introducing tiny amounts of the allergen and then slowly increasing the dose over time, the immune system gradually becomes used to the allergen. _Eventually over ~2 years, the body becomes trained to tolerate doses of the allergen it previously could not_.

OIT has two phases: 1) build-up and 2) maintenance.

